      "writtenOn": "2020-09-18T12:34:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For injecting data, I would strongly recommend something like we do for Gold, where we set some   constant values on window and have a way to access them. \nhttps://github.com/google/skia-buildbot/blob/master/golden/modules/settings.js\n\nI think the way Gold does it is more clear \"where the data comes from\" and allows for easier mocking/injection during tests.\n\nOtherwise, you would have to pass repos into status which would have to pass it into commits-table-sk. That seems like a lot of boilerplate for a constant list. This gets even more hectic the more data that is added or if data needs to get injected deep.",
      "revId": "fb189a2c3dffcb6bfe8981e63697e2d79ec27971",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
